title: Database Connection Pool - Query with Retry

participant Application as App
participant Connection Pool as Pool
participant DB Connection as Conn
participant PostgreSQL as DB

App->>Pool: getConnection()
note over Pool: Pool size: 3/10 active
Pool-->>App: Connection #4
App->>Conn: BEGIN
Conn->>DB: BEGIN
DB-->>Conn: OK
App->>Conn: SELECT * FROM accounts WHERE id=$1
Conn->>DB: Execute prepared statement
DB-->>Conn: ResultSet (1 row)
Conn-->>App: Row { id: 42, balance: 1500 }
App->>Conn: UPDATE accounts SET balance=balance-200
Conn->>DB: Execute prepared statement
DB-->>Conn: ERROR: deadlock detected
note right of Conn: Transaction aborted
Conn-->>App: DatabaseError (deadlock)
App->>Conn: ROLLBACK
Conn->>DB: ROLLBACK
DB-->>Conn: OK
note over App: Retry attempt 1 (backoff: 50ms)
App->>Conn: BEGIN
Conn->>DB: BEGIN
DB-->>Conn: OK
App->>Conn: UPDATE accounts SET balance=balance-200
Conn->>DB: Execute prepared statement
DB-->>Conn: UPDATE 1
App->>Conn: COMMIT
Conn->>DB: COMMIT
DB-->>Conn: OK
Conn-->>App: Success
App->>Pool: releaseConnection(#4)
note over Pool: Connection returned, 3/10 active
